[49m[38;5;9m- 104     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Amazon S3 for slide storage.** Whole slide images are large (2-5 GB each), write-once, and read-many. S3 provides durable, encrypted storage with lifecycle policies to tier older slides to cheaper storage classes. The S3 access patterns (random byte-range reads for tile serving) are well-supported.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon S3 for slide storage.** Whole slide images are large (2-5 GB each), write-once, and read-many. S3 provides durable, encrypted storage with lifecycle policies to tier older slides to cheaper storage classes. The S3 access patterns (random byte-range reads for tile serving) are well-supported. For on-premises scanners, use AWS DataSync or Storage Gateway to handle the transfer reliably; budget 100+ Mbps dedicated bandwidth for a lab processing 200+ slides per day.
